## 10-Step Sequence Map

| Step | Pillar | Service |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | AI Systems & Automation | AI Agents and Automation |
| 2 | AI Strategy & Innovation | AI Roadmap Accelerator |
| 3 | AI Intelligence & Personalization | AI-Driven Personalization |
| 4 | AI Systems & Automation | Marketing Operations Automation |
| 5 | Strategy | Revenue Marketing Transformation |
| 6 | Operations | Revenue Operations |
| 7 | Technology Consulting | HubSpot Services |
| 8 | AI Intelligence | Data and Decision Intelligence |
| 9 | Managed Services & Creative | Demand Generation |
| 10 | Revenue Marketing Transformation | Meeting close |

---

## Industry Personas

The server resolves the HubSpot `industry` property to one of 19 built-in vertical personas. Each persona contains industry-specific pain points, AI opportunity narrative, benchmark stats, tone guidance, and opening hook scenarios.

**Supported verticals:**
Technology, Computer Software, Internet/Digital, Financial Services, Banking, Insurance, Healthcare, Biotechnology, Pharmaceuticals, Industrial Automation/Manufacturing, Machinery, Management Consulting, Accounting, Retail, Media & Entertainment, Higher Education, Staffing & Recruiting, Real Estate, Telecommunications, Nonprofit

Unmatched industries fall back to a DEFAULT B2B persona. The resolver runs three passes: exact match → partial match → reverse partial match → DEFAULT.

---

## Endpoints

| Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|
| `GET /` | Health check — returns queue length, in-flight count, error count, domains cached, contacts completed |
| `GET /dashboard` | Live queue monitor — auto-refreshes every 5 seconds |
| `GET /errors` | Error log viewer — shows all permanent failures with contact ID, step, error message, and timestamp |
| `POST /enqueue` | Receives contact payloads from HubSpot workflow |

---

## Persistent Files (Render /tmp)

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `/tmp/domain_cache.json` | Scraped company website data — 7 day TTL, survives restarts |
| `/tmp/completed.log` | Record of every successfully processed contact — prevents re-processing on restart |
| `/tmp/errors.log` | Record of every permanent failure — viewable at `/errors` |

---

## Processing Speed

| Setting | Jobs/min | 10k contacts |
|---|---|---|
| CONCURRENCY 3, interval 1500ms | ~22 | ~7.5 hours |
| CONCURRENCY 6, interval 1000ms | ~42 | ~4 hours |
| CONCURRENCY 7, interval 1000ms | ~52 | ~3 hours |

**Current setting:** CONCURRENCY 6, PROCESS_INTERVAL_MS 1000 (~4 hours for 10k contacts)

---

## Deployment

1. Push `server.js` and `package.json` to a GitHub repo
2. Create a new Web Service on Render, connect the repo
3. Set environment variables (`HUBSPOT_TOKEN`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`)
4. Deploy — Render runs `node server.js` automatically
5. Copy your Render URL into the HubSpot custom code steps
6. Enroll contacts in the HubSpot workflow

---

## Adding a New Industry Persona

1. Find the `INDUSTRY_PERSONAS` object in `server.js`
2. Copy an existing persona block
3. Change the key to match the normalized HubSpot industry value (uppercase, underscores, no special characters)
4. Rewrite the 5 pain points, AI opportunity, stats, tone note, and opening hooks for the new vertical
5. Redeploy

To find unmapped industries in your database: HubSpot → Contacts → filter by Industry → export and count distinct values. Any industry falling through to DEFAULT will appear in the server logs as `⚠️ No industry match for: "X". Using DEFAULT.`
